                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.652,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 59288,
                                "text": "No. 02-6683 Castro against the United States will be announced by Justice Breyer."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.652,
                        "stop": 310.222,
                        "byte_start": 59288,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.652,
                                "stop": 11.497,
                                "byte_start": 59288,
                                "byte_stop": 74752,
                                "text": "This is a little complicated, Habeas case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.497,
                                "stop": 25.34,
                                "byte_start": 74752,
                                "byte_stop": 130132,
                                "text": "The federal prisoner, when the prisoner filed a 2255 motion commonly known as a habeas corpus motion, he might find himself without a habeas corpus remedy for a rather special reason."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.34,
                                "stop": 34.063,
                                "byte_start": 130132,
                                "byte_stop": 164927,
                                "text": "Imagine that before filing this motion, at some earlier time, he filed a different motion that he used the wrong name for."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.063,
                                "stop": 40.102,
                                "byte_start": 164927,
                                "byte_stop": 189168,
                                "text": "He called it a Rule 33 motion, but it should have been called a 2255 motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.102,
                                "stop": 49.934,
                                "byte_start": 189168,
                                "byte_stop": 228456,
                                "text": "Now, imagine that the judge in that first hearing noticing that the litigant did not have a lawyer, he was preceding pro se, said I will re-characterize that motion for you."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.934,
                                "stop": 54.853,
                                "byte_start": 228456,
                                "byte_stop": 248101,
                                "text": "I will call it a 2255 motion, i.e. a habeas motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.853,
                                "stop": 63.872,
                                "byte_start": 248101,
                                "byte_stop": 284254,
                                "text": "And imagine that the judge did that because he really thought that 2255 more aptly suited the nature of the litigant\u2019s claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.872,
                                "stop": 67.301,
                                "byte_start": 284254,
                                "byte_stop": 297942,
                                "text": "And the litigant, not being a lawyer, did not say anything."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.301,
                                "stop": 77.17,
                                "byte_start": 297942,
                                "byte_stop": 337439,
                                "text": "Now, we are at our proceeding where he files his 2255 motion, but the government will claim you already did that, this is your second habeas motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.17,
                                "stop": 85.649,
                                "byte_start": 337439,
                                "byte_stop": 371294,
                                "text": "Since it is your second habeas motion, you have to meet special very rigorous requirements that apply to a second but not a first one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.649,
                                "stop": 90.195,
                                "byte_start": 371294,
                                "byte_stop": 389475,
                                "text": "And therefore this second one, says the government, will be dismissed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.195,
                                "stop": 112.06,
                                "byte_start": 389475,
                                "byte_stop": 476933,
                                "text": "The prisoner says \u201coh my goodness, if only I had known at that earlier time what was going to happen to me if I allowed the judge to call this first motion the 2255 motion, I never would have done it or maybe I would have withdrawn it, but I would have done something anyway because I would have wanted to keep my chance to file a habeas motion later.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.06,
                                "stop": 131.912,
                                "byte_start": 476933,
                                "byte_stop": 556345,
                                "text": "Well, that is what this case is about, and we are asked whether a judge should at least warn the pro se litigant, that first judge, about the potential consequences of what would happen if he re-characterized the motion and what would happen if he does not re-characterized the motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.912,
                                "stop": 141.305,
                                "byte_start": 556345,
                                "byte_stop": 593962,
                                "text": "Now in our opinion, we hold first, contrary to what the government argued, that we do have jurisdiction at leads to consider this question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.305,
                                "stop": 156.324,
                                "byte_start": 593962,
                                "byte_stop": 654043,
                                "text": "True, the habeas statute bars us from considering a lower court\u2019s decision to grant or deny a litigant\u2019s request to file any 2255 motion after the first, but in this case the litigant never asked for or denied permission."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.324,
                                "stop": 162.554,
                                "byte_start": 654043,
                                "byte_stop": 678912,
                                "text": "He is just talking about whether that first motion was his first or second, and we can answer the question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.554,
                                "stop": 180.82,
                                "byte_start": 678912,
                                "byte_stop": 752055,
                                "text": "Now what we go on to hold on the question in exercising our supervisory powers that the lower court\u2019s power, that first judge, his power to re-characterize a motion as the first 2255, i.e. as a first habeas, that power is limited."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.82,
                                "stop": 182.694,
                                "byte_start": 752055,
                                "byte_stop": 759474,
                                "text": "Now how is it limited?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.694,
                                "stop": 191.708,
                                "byte_start": 759474,
                                "byte_stop": 795523,
                                "text": "Well, the limitation applies when a court re-characterizes a pro se litigant\u2019s motion as a first 2255 motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.708,
                                "stop": 197.064,
                                "byte_start": 795523,
                                "byte_stop": 816943,
                                "text": "In other words, the judge is saying \u201cwhat you filed as a 33, is not a 3, it is a 2255.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.064,
                                "stop": 198.835,
                                "byte_start": 816943,
                                "byte_stop": 824048,
                                "text": "That is our situation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.835,
                                "stop": 205.978,
                                "byte_start": 824048,
                                "byte_stop": 852679,
                                "text": "Now in those circumstances, the District Court has to notify the pro se litigant that it is going to do this."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.978,
                                "stop": 233.606,
                                "byte_start": 852679,
                                "byte_stop": 963124,
                                "text": "That it is going to re-characterize the pleading, and he has to warn the litigant that this re-characterization means that any subsequent habeas motion is going to be subject to those restrictions that apply to second or successive habeas motion, and he has to say to the litigant \u201cyou now have the opportunity to withdraw the motion or amend it so it contains all the habeas claims you think you have.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.606,
                                "stop": 250.01,
                                "byte_start": 963124,
                                "byte_stop": 1028744,
                                "text": "Now if the court fails to do that, then the consequence is that the motion cannot be considered to become a 2255 motion for purposes of applying to later motions the law\u2019s second or successive requirement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 250.01,
                                "stop": 266.248,
                                "byte_start": 1028744,
                                "byte_stop": 1093736,
                                "text": "In other words, unless the first judge warns the pro se litigant about the potential consequences of the re-characterization a subsequently filed habeas motion has to be treated as the first not the second habeas motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 266.248,
                                "stop": 279.907,
                                "byte_start": 1093736,
                                "byte_stop": 1148385,
                                "text": "Now because in this case the pro se litigant\u2019s Rule 33 motion was re-characterized without any warning, the subsequent 2255 motion should not have been treated as his second it should have been treated as his first."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 279.907,
                                "stop": 283.768,
                                "byte_start": 1148385,
                                "byte_stop": 1163745,
                                "text": "We therefore vacate and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.768,
                                "stop": 310.222,
                                "byte_start": 1163745,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in our resolution of the jurisdictional question and concurring in the judgment which Justice Thomas joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
